cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

The paper deals with the memoryless determinacy of infinite parity games, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and logic. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves game theory, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of induction and transfinite induction suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the mention of applications in computer science suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
